      <h1 class='title'>Entry Clearance</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 December 2002 vol 396 c34WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_34ws' title='Col. 34WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 December 2002 vol 396 c34WS' name='column_34ws' href='#column_34ws' rel='bookmark'>34WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0396P0_20021216_CWS_4'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-bill-rammell' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0396P0_20021216_CWS_4' title='Link to this speech by Mr Bill Rammell' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-bill-rammell" title="Mr Bill Rammell">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs (Mr. Bill Rammell)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">I have arranged for copies of the second annual report by Rabinder Singh QC, the Independent monitor for Entry Clearance Refusals to be laid before the House today. I welcome Mr. Singh's report and note his comments and suggestions, which will receive careful consideration.</p><p>Mr. Singh has not sought to extend his appointment beyond 30 november 2002 and I thank Mr. Singh for all his hard work and dedication during his two years as Independent Monitor for Entry Clearance.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
